&lt;p&gt;Lead Nurse –Deteriorating Patient&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whittington Health has created an innovative position within Critical Care services. The successful candidate will support the trust’s deteriorating patient agenda by providing visible nurse leadership to the 10 bedded Critical Care Unit and the Critical Care Outreach Team. As an expert Critical Care practitioner you will have the opportunity to ensure that the highest standards of nursing care is given to patients requiring level 2 or 3 care across the trust. Working closely with the Clinical Manager for Deteriorating Patient and Resuscitation services, Clinical Lead and General Manager, you will ensure that staff in all areas of the trust deliver the highest standards of patient care, and that deteriorating patients are recognised and managed appropriately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior nurse leader in the trust, you will be expected to be able to advise and contribute to the Critical Care and Nursing and Midwifery strategy. . You will be expected to contribute to the financial stability of the service and be responsible for environment, infection control, quality and patient experience within the service. You will be an exemplary nursing leader role model at all times in presence, communication and behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
